Coast security chiefs have been blamed for the Monday night burglary in a human rights activist&rsquo;s home. Muhuri chairman Khalif Khelef&rsquo;s house in Nyali,Mombasa, was raided by unknown men. Abdul Khalif was sleeping in the house. He said a man in a hooded jacket and others surrounded the compound.Khelef said the gang only took three phones, leaving other valuables.He said no arrests have been made, even after he reported the attack. Khelef was not in the house during the incident as he is in Europe on a work-related trip.